nodes.bodyText:
I like the builder pattern here. I used something similar for Kite's InputFormat.
You might consider how that builder worked. The static methods there would accept a Job when creating the builder. That way, there was no need for the user to also set the input format class. It was also not necessary to build the resulting Configuration and do something with it:
  /**
   * Configures the {@code Job} to use the {@code IcebergInputFormat} and
   * returns a helper to add further configuration.
   *
   * @param job the {@code Job} to configure
   */
  public static ConfigBuilder configure(Job job) {
    job.setInputFormatClass(IcebergInputFormat.class);
    return new ConfigBuilder(job.getConfiguration());
  }

