In Spark, this is an instance method so that user can override it and use their own catalog. I think that would be a good idea here as well:
public class CustomCatalogIcebergInputFormat extends IcebergInputFormat {
  @Override
  public Table getTable(String tablePath) {
    CustomCatalog.get().loadTable(conf.get(tablePath));
  }
}
In that example, I'm assuming that we'd have a final getTable(Configuration) method that pulls TABLE_PATH out of the config and passes it to getTable.

