Yeah, I guess that's not a good way to inject a catalog. In addition, the configuration methods sets up the IcebergInputFormat and not a user's subclass.
I think the factory idea would work, but it's more of a Supplier<Catalog> since there is no configuration. Like this?
  ConfigBuilder catalogSupplier(Class<? extends Supplier<Catalog>> supplierClass)) {
    this.supplierClass = supplierClass;
    return this;
